# RDMA_TRAFFIC_GEN
## DESCRIPSION 
 Monitor behavior of nccl_tests, but using self-defined perftest to read trace input.
## HOW_TO BUILD
For mpi program
 ```
cd /path/to/rdma_traffic_gen/perftest/trace_write_bw
mpicc write_bw_simple.c -o mpi_launch_write_bw
 ```

For write_bw
```
cd /path/to/rdma_traffic_gen/perftest/
./autogen.sh
./configure
make
##but !DO NOT! make install 
```

## HOW_TO_RUN
Modify the hosts setting in your ~/.ssh/config and hosts file under directory trace_write_bw to fit environment setting.
And use mpirun to launch threads across hosts.
```
cd /path/to/rdma_traffic_gen/perftest/trace_write_bw

mpirun -np 3 --hostfile hosts ./mpi_launch_write_bw /home/rdma_traffic_gen/perftest/ib_write_bw -d mlx5_0 -x 3
```
## FOR DEVELOPMENT
Modify perftest/write_bw.c and trace_write_bw/write_bw_simple.c 

